Virus neutralizing assays showed that the serum from mice treated with pVAX1-(PEDV-S1) plus pVAX1-(IL-18) developed 1:40 and 1:20 neutralizing antibodies that significantly (p
 < 0.01) neutralized the virus relative to pVAX1-(PEDV-S1) only and control immunized mice (Fig. 5
). Significant neutralization was observed at serum dilutions of both 1:20 and 1:40.
